Class Double2IntMaps.Singleton

java.lang.Object
it.unimi.dsi.fastutil.doubles.AbstractDouble2IntFunction

it.unimi.dsi.fastutil.doubles.Double2IntMaps.Singleton
All Implemented Interfaces:

Direct Known Subclasses:
Double2IntSortedMaps.Singleton
Enclosing class:
Double2IntMaps
public static class Double2IntMaps.Singleton extends Double2IntFunctions.Singleton implements Double2IntMap, Serializable, Cloneable
An immutable class representing a type-specific singleton map.

This class may be useful to implement your own in case you subclass a type-specific map.

    • double2IntEntrySet

      public ObjectSet<Double2IntMap.Entry> double2IntEntrySet()
      Description copied from interface: Double2IntMap
      Returns a type-specific set view of the mappings contained in this map.

      This method is necessary because there is no inheritance along type parameters: it is thus impossible to strengthen Map.entrySet() so that it returns an ObjectSet of type-specific entries (the latter makes it possible to access keys and values with type-specific methods).

      Specified by:
      double2IntEntrySet in interface Double2IntMap
